<setup>
  <selectFromSequence name = "a" from = "3" to = "9" step = "1"/>
  <selectFromSequence name = "b" from = "-5" to = "5" step = "1" exclude="0 1"/>
  <selectFromSequence name = "c" from = "-3" to = "3" step = "1" exclude="0 1"/>
  <selectFromSequence name = "d" from = "1" to = "7" step = "1" exclude="$b $c"/>

  <function name="f">x^$c*($a)^x</function>
  <derivative name="fP">$f</derivative>
  
  <function name="g"><math simplify>x^(1/$d)*cos(x)</math></function>
  <derivative name="gP">$g</derivative>

  <function name="h">$b * cos(x) * sin(x)</function>
  <derivative name="hP">$h</derivative>

  <function name="p">($c*\cos(x) + $d*\sin(x))(x^($a) + ($d+1)^x)</function>
  <derivative name="pP">$p</derivative>
  
</setup>

<p>
  For each of the following functions, use appropriate basic derivative rules along with the product rule to find a formula for the function's derivative.  You need not algebraically simplify your derivative formulas.
</p>  

<p>
  <ol marker="a.">
    <li>
      <p>
        If <m>f(x) = x^{$c} \cdot $a^x</m>, then <m>f'(x)=</m><answer>$fP</answer>.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        If <m>g(x) = x^{\frac{1}{$d}} \cdot \cos(x)</m>, then <m>g'(x)= </m><answer>$gP</answer>.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        If <m>h(x)= $$h(x)</m>, then <m>h'(x)= </m><answer>$hP</answer>.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        If <m>p(x)= ($c \cos(x) + $d \sin(x))(x^{$a} + <math simplify>($d+1)</math>^x)</m>, then <m>p'(x)= </m><answer>$pP</answer>.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol>  
</p>  